text: Had been taking in the sights all day needed food in a hurry before show, hit the spot devious burger

Everything was very salty. This is the second time we eat at Five Guys. The one in Greenwich Village was great, but this one was disappointing, mainly because the amount of salt in the food. It made it very hard to eat.

The manager completely flipped out on her employees in front of everyone. It was very uncomfortable and she is very rude. I would never come back here. I feel so bad they have to work for such an abusive boss

I am a vegetarian and I got a veggie lover sandwich, it was not worth the money as it was just plain vegetables on a piece of bread with no seasoning. The grilled cheese was even worse for the same price. And sadly no free peanuts.

Disappointing! Everyone hypes 5 guys. The fries were too salty and the beef was SO incredibly dry. Just a chewy, saucy, salty mess. Definitely not the worst burger I've ever had but not worth the hype or price. If you really want burgers from a chain restaurant, go get shake shack.

There is a lot of smell of marihuana, which comes from outside. At the end I tried to get one cup in order to swith my fries and use a lid to cover them. When I asked about it the guy in charge told me that I needed to pay 4 dollar for that cup.

This place need new staff , I believe they step on every burger that comes out . Horrible experience , for every group coming in the staff look at each other and say " that's not true " and the place wasn't even full...
The worst 5 guys i ever been. All dumb people working there

You go for the burgers not the atmosphere.  Big tasty burgers with tons of toppings.  Barrels of peanuts to munch on while waiting for orders.  Fries are big enough to share for multiple people.  a number of locations have new soda machine that can dispense any of 100 different sodas

The burgers are always cooked well done, as they don't allow cooking to your desired temperature. Fries were soggy and probably reheated twice. I'm always wondering how this chain manages to open so many locations with such below-par products.

From the time I placed my order...BAD EXPERIENCE.  SIGN at register states EXACT PAYMENT OR DEBIT/CREDIT CARD. My order took 20 minutes to complete because the staff was playing around instead of working. The seating was being held as a hangout for tourists.  And when they did leave tables weren't sanitized.  A MESS AND COVID INVITE

The food is amazing, the staff is really friendly, but the place had an awful smell like chlorine mixed with a dirty bathroom smell and mold. Had to take out because I couldn't have sat there and eaten.

The service was friendly, but the meat was not what was advertised. They have all those nice articles hanging around about how juicy their meat is, but at least mine was dry and the taste was mediocre. Nothing you wouldn't get at any fast food chain.
Place looked and felt so ghetto we didn't stay. Looking at the burgers being made, didn't look like we were missing out either. Went to Shake Shack instead and had a great experience there.
Worst hamburger ever. Tasteless, unshaped, and couldn't Even finish the coke. Worst 15 dollars spent in a really long time

Food and service was good but way too packed, no seats and everyone is on top of each other. The location has a lot of tourists so makes sense but I wouldn't recy going during the holiday season, just way too busy and hard to get seat

Food was average I have been to five guys before on the west coast but this didn't live up to the general quality of food. Perhaps the chef's were having a bad day but the beef was overcooked and dry and the presentation was lack luster even by the usual standard

the woman who takes orders is so rude and unkind. I think that's because i'm Asian. What i did was only change my menu while ordering, she said "oh my god" and treated me as if i'm an idiot. the taste of burger is just soso and a bit greasy. I don't want to visit again here.

Ordered online. Arrived a few minutes after the meal was supposed to be ready. When I got there, they told me my meal was on the table being prepared. After a while, they realize it was already done and in a bag, just sitting there and getting colder.
Fries were bussin, burger was insanely good, it was my first time eating Five Guys food and I just want to go back!.
The worst Five Guys I've been into. The employers don't spread the values that the company has. Everything was dirty.
My first five guys, and either this one is not representative, or the emperor has no clothes.  Limp wet fries.  The burger was good but very ordinary.
Really slow. No shakes. Small. And the order taker never asked what I wanted on my burger (luckily, I noticed the error on my receipt).
Soggy fries, slow service and the entire bag was so soggy I couldn't tell if the bun was even toasted. 1/5 probably will make the mistake of going here again though.
Too many people and no provisions in place to handle them. It was one big Moshe pit with no real way out. The Xmas setup is nice but not worth the fight to see it.
You will be kicked out if you are a party of 5 or more, they don't serve you.
Terrible burgers and fries. As greasy as can be. Depressing place. Not cheap. Waste of time and money
Burger is above average.  Not the best. Fries are over cooked
Easily crowded, difficult to find seat.
Took 50 min for a chesseburguer and a hotdog and the local wasn't full.
They appear to simply throw the food together without paying attention to the presentation.  You're paying 10 dollars for a burger at least make it look appealing.
I went in to get something to go, the greeter said to order from the bar and the bartender told me they don't take orders and that was it, like I don't count.  I left.
Can't think of better burgers, hot dogs and fries in NYC than Five Guys, so yummy.
Extremely rude staff. Bad attitude and bad manners. Never going to visit this place again.
The service was very slow we asked for the food for eat in and they gave it to us in a paper bag and the peanuts were empty which is one of the Staples of this restaurant
If you are a New York and you want to eat a burger there is no choice... You have to go here.
Hmmmmm eat until you die but not this burger it's hmmmmm

It doesn't seem like Five Guys anymore, it's gotten a lot worse. It was my favorite burger. Not anymore. I found the environment very dirty and the sandwich very greasy. The fries were horrible, to the point that we didn't eat them.

It took them about 10 minutes to receive the order and even though they had almost no customers, it took another 12 minutes for the burger to be ready, they left it lying in a corner until someone went to ask for the order. I'm not coming back here.
